Definition.WordDefinition: Primates \Pri*ma"tes\, n. pl. [NL.] (Zo["o]l.) The highest order of mammals. It includes man, together with the apes and monkeys. Cf. {Pitheci}. [1913 Webster]
Primates n : an animal order including lemurs and tarsiers and monkeys and apes and human beings [syn: {order Primates}]
